<subSubSection id="C300C4894849292C6FC853999E2140FC" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA597024849292C6FC853999E2140FC" blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B96E4B104849292C6FC853999D544187" bold="true" box="[199,327,191,217]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AEC814849292C6EB353E69E974187" authority="Santos, 2007" authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2007" box="[444,644,192,217]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96E4B104849292C6EB353E69E974187" box="[444,644,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Architis colombo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96E4B104849292C6D8453999EFB4187" bold="true" box="[651,744,191,217]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25DF66B4849292C6D8453999EFB4187" box="[651,744,191,217]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differ from those of other species of the genus by the anteriorly directed DTP and the large, ventrally projected prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia (
<figureCitation id="13218B874849292C6A2C53CE999C405C" box="[1315,1423,232,258]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
). The females resemble 
<taxonomicName id="4C1AEC814849292C6EA552369E734077" authority="Santos, 2007" authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="2007" box="[426,608,272,297]" class="Arachnida" family="Pisauridae" genus="Architis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fritzmuelleri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96E4B104849292C6EA552369E734077" box="[426,608,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. fritzmuelleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96E4B104849292C6D6552299ED84077" bold="true" box="[618,715,271,297]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25DF66B4849292C6D6552299ED84077" box="[618,715,271,297]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the anteriorly positioned copulatory openings and wide, strongly sclerotised CD. They can be distinguished by the small, posteriorly rounded median field, the anterior sclerotised hoods over the lateral lobes of the epigynum and by the absence of enlarged copulatory atria in the internal genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13218B874849292C6E9852AE9E3740FC" box="[407,548,392,418]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 14E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C300C4894849292C6FC852899DE0444C" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA597024849292C6FC852899D4B4097" blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" box="[199,344,431,457]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B96E4B104849292C6FC852899D4B4097" bold="true" box="[199,344,431,457]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA597024849292C6FC852F19F1240AC" blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" box="[199,769,471,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B96E4B104849292C6FC852F19D1540AF" bold="true" box="[199,262,471,497]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male</emphasis>
(
<materialsCitation id="3B729D5F4849292C6E1A52FE9F1240AC" box="[277,769,472,498]" country="Brazil" location="Colombo" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
based on 
<typeStatus id="54A129A04849292C6E8952FE9DFF40AC" box="[390,492,472,498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<location id="8EC5C1D94849292C6D3B52FE9EB740AC" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B32614484F292C6F98541C99174464:8EC5C1D94849292C6D3B52FE9EB740AC" box="[564,676,472,498]" country="Brazil" name="Colombo" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Colombo</location>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30DD7924849292C6DBF52FE9EEA40AC" box="[688,761,472,498]" name="Brazil" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Brazil</collectingCountry>
)
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA597024849292C6FC85126998F42F4" blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Carapace brown, with a median and two lateral pale brown stripes from a posterior pale brown area to the ocular area (
<figureCitation id="13218B874849292C6E22510E9D8F431C" box="[301,412,552,578]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Anterior eye row procurved, median eyes slightly larger than lateral eyes. Posterior eyes of similar size, approximately 1.5 times the diameter of anterior median eyes. Clypeus brown, chelicerae pale brown with a median dark spot anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13218B874849292C6DFC515E9F7743CC" box="[755,868,632,658]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
). Labium and endites brown, sternum creamcoloured. Pedipalpi cream-coloured, with an apical brown ring on femur. Cymbium reddish-brown. Legs pale brown, with four dark rings on femora and scattered dark spots on other segments. Opisthosoma brown with a median and two lateral pale brown stripes from middle to anterior margin (
<figureCitation id="13218B874849292C6B3D51D698B04254" box="[1074,1187,752,778]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma sides brown with a median pale brown spot. Venter dark brown, pale at the margins and the epigastric plate. Spinnerets pale brown, darker on ectal sides. Total length 2.9; carapace 1.3 long, 1.4 wide. Tibia I length 1.8, II 1.7, III 1.0, IV 1.4. Opisthosoma 1.5 long, 1.1 wide. VTA rounded, projected dorsally to vRTA (
<figureCitation id="13218B874849292C6A2F504E999D42DC" box="[1312,1422,872,898]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
); vRTA projected ventrally, with a small ventral knob (
<figureCitation id="13218B874849292C6C0F50B69F9D42F4" box="[768,910,912,938]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14C, D</figureCitation>
); dRTA small, shorter than vRTA (
<figureCitation id="13218B874849292C6A2D50B6999C42F4" box="[1314,1423,912,938]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[205,1380,354,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-133@27.[173,1424,308,1935]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 14A–F. Architis colombo sp. nov. A, female habitus, dorsal view; B, female prosoma, frontal view; C, male pedipalpus, ventral view; D, male pedipalpus, lateral view; E, female epigynum, ventral view; F, female internal genitalia, dorsal view. The arrow points to the prolateral excavation of the pedipalpal tibia. Scale bars: A–B, 0.5 mm; C–D, 0.2 mm; E–F, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5097215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5097215/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA597024849292C6FC850919804428C" blockId="28.[151,1437,151,1338]" box="[199,1047,951,978]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="B96E4B104849292C6FC850919D31428F" bold="true" box="[199,290,951,977]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Female</emphasis>
(
<materialsCitation id="3B729D5F4849292C6E3E509E9804428C" accessionNumber="MCN 25131" box="[305,1047,952,978]" collectionCode="MCN" collectorName="de Caldas" country="Brazil" location="Pocos de Caldas" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="paratype">
